  "statement": {
    "title": "EmbeddingBag produces wrong results when input is 2D and include_last_offset is True",
    "body": "When using `nn.EmbeddingBag` with a 2D input tensor and `include_last_offset=True`, the offsets are computed incorrectly, leading to wrong aggregation results. The issue is in how `torch.nn.functional.embedding_bag` constructs the offsets tensor when the input is already 2D \u2014 it fails to account for `include_last_offset` properly.",
    "labels": [
      "module: nn",
      "bug",
      "module: sparse"
    ]
